Generovanie AR(1)

Na generovanie ARMA a ARIMA procesov sli prkaz arima.sim()

Vygenerujte proces \(X_t-0,8X_{t-1}=Z_t\)

n = 100
ar1 = arima.sim(list(ar=0.8),n)
plot(ar1, main = 'Vygenerovany AR(1) proces', type='o')
abline(0,0)

Vygenerujte niekoko realizci.

Pozorovanie:

  • bez trendu
  • str. hodnota okolo 0
  • zrejme stacionrny
  • nie je to biely um!
  • porovnanm s hladinou Hurnskeho jazera vidme, e sa podobaj

Vygenerujte proces \(X_t+0,8X_{t-1}=Z_t\)

n = 100
ar1 = arima.sim(list(ar=-0.8),n)
plot(ar1, main = 'Vygenerovany AR(1) proces', type='o')
abline(0,0)

  • Zhluky s pravidelnejie
  • astejie sa striedaj hodnoty s +/-

Zobrazi oba grafy do jednho obrzku kvli lepiemu porovnaniu:

n = 100
ar1a = arima.sim(list(ar=0.8),n)
ar1b = arima.sim(list(ar=-0.8),n)
par(mfrow=c(2,1))
plot(ar1a, main = 'Vygenerovany AR(1) proces', type='o')
abline(0,0)
plot(ar1b, main = 'Vygenerovany AR(1) proces', type='o')
abline(0,0)

Syntax pre ubovon ARMA(p,q):

arima.sim(list(ar=c(\(\phi_1, \phi_2, \dots,\phi_p\)), ma=c(\(\theta_1, \theta_2, \dots, \theta_q\))),n)

Syntax pre ubovon ARIMA(p,d,q):

arima.sim(list(order=(p,q,d),ar=c(\(\phi_1, \phi_2, \dots,\phi_p\)), ma=c(\(\theta_1, \theta_2, \dots, \theta_q\))),n)
